            <li>
              <strong>Compliance Admin</strong>: Full access to all compliance features
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Compliance Auditor</strong>: Read-only access to compliance reports
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Regular User</strong>: Limited access to compliance data related to their actions
            </li>
          </ul>
          
          <div class="mt-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 font-medium">To set up these permissions:</p>
            <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 mt-1 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
              <li>Navigate to <strong>Accounts</strong> > <strong>Users</strong></li>
              <li>Select a user and click <strong>Edit Permissions</strong></li>
              <li>Under the Compliance section, set appropriate role</li>
              <li>Click <strong>Save Changes</strong></li>
            </ol>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <h3 class="mt-6">2. Configure Compliance Settings</h3>
      
