        <div class="p-4">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
            Set up global compliance settings to meet your regulatory and business requirements:
          </p>
          
          <div class="mt-4">
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 font-medium">Steps to configure global settings:</p>
            <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 mt-1 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
              <li>Navigate to <strong>Settings</strong> > <strong>Compliance</strong></li>
              <li>Configure the following settings:
                <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-1">
                  <li><strong>Retention Period</strong>: How long to keep compliance records (default: 7 years)</li>
                  <li><strong>Consent Expiration</strong>: Default expiration for consent records (if applicable)</li>
                  <li><strong>Required Proof</strong>: Level of evidence required for consent (IP, user agent, etc.)</li>
                  <li><strong>Report Signing</strong>: Enable/disable cryptographic signing of reports</li>
                  <li><strong>Automatic Logging</strong>: Configure which events are automatically logged</li>
