    <section id="validation" class="py-6 border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
      <h2>Validation Rules</h2>
      
      <p>
        Validation rules ensure data quality and compliance with regulatory requirements. They can be configured 
        at different levels (vertical, campaign, field) and with different severity levels.
      </p>
      
      <h3 class="mt-6">Types of Validation Rules</h3>
      
      <div class="my-4 bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 divide-y md:divide-y-0 md:divide-x divide-gray-200 dark:divide-gray-700">
          <div class="p-4">
            <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Condition Rules</h4>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1">
              Use a Ruby-like DSL to create complex conditions.
            </p>
            <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 mt-2 p-3 rounded text-xs font-mono text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 overflow-auto">
              # Example: Ensure age is 18+ if financial product is selected<br>
              field('age').to_i >= 18 if field('product_type') == 'financial'
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="p-4">
            <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Pattern Rules</h4>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1">
              Validate fields against regex patterns.
            </p>
            <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 mt-2 p-3 rounded text-xs font-mono text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 overflow-auto">
              # Example: Ensure valid format for SSN<br>
              field('ssn').match?(/^\d{3}-\d{2}-\d{4}$/)
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="p-4">
            <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Lookup Rules</h4>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1">
              Check field values against predefined lists.
            </p>
            <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 mt-2 p-3 rounded text-xs font-mono text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 overflow-auto">
              # Example: Ensure state is valid US state<br>
              VALID_STATES.include?(field('state').upcase)
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="p-4">
            <h4 class="font-medium text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Dependency Rules</h4>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1">
              Ensure dependent fields are provided when required.
            </p>
            <div class="bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800 mt-2 p-3 rounded text-xs font-mono text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 overflow-auto">
              # Example: If phone_consent is true, require phone number<br>
              !field('phone_consent') || field('phone').present?
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <h3 class="mt-6">Setting Up Validation Rules</h3>
      
      <div class="my-4 bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <div class="p-4">
          <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 space-y-3 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
            <li>
              Navigate to <strong>Validation Rules</strong>
            </li>
            <li>
              Click <strong>Create New Rule</strong>
            </li>
            <li>
              Configure the rule:
              <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-1">
                <li><strong>Name</strong>: Descriptive name for the rule</li>
                <li><strong>Description</strong>: Detailed explanation of what the rule checks</li>
                <li><strong>Rule Type</strong>: Select from the available types</li>
                <li><strong>Condition</strong>: Enter the validation expression</li>
                <li><strong>Error Message</strong>: Message to display when validation fails</li>
                <li><strong>Severity</strong>: Choose from:
                  <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-1">
                    <li><strong>Error</strong>: Prevents submission</li>
                    <li><strong>Warning</strong>: Allows submission but flags for review</li>
                    <li><strong>Info</strong>: Informational only, doesn't block submission</li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li><strong>Scope</strong>: Where the rule applies (Vertical, Campaign, or Field)</li>
                <li><strong>Position</strong>: Order in which rules are evaluated</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
              Click <strong>Save Rule</strong>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <h3 class="mt-6">Testing Validation Rules</h3>
      
      <div class="my-4 bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <div class="p-4 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          <p>Before deploying a validation rule:</p>
          
          <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 mt-3 space-y-2">
            <li>Navigate to <strong>Validation Rules</strong> > select your rule</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Test Rule</strong></li>
            <li>Enter test values for the fields referenced in the rule</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Run Test</strong> to verify the rule works as expected</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
